    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka opposition leader vows to have ex-MP Ranjan Ramanayake back in parliament",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s main opposition the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) will reappoint former MP Ranjan Ramanayake, who is to be released from prison on a presidential pardon,\u00a0 in the first instance a national list vacancy is available, SJB leader Sajith Premadasa said.",
        "Shortly after it was announced that President Ranil Wickremesinghe had signed a conditional pardon for Ramanayake, Premadasa tweeted Friday August 26 afternoon that he pledged to bring Ramanayake back into parliament\u2019s fold.",
        "We the @sjbsrilanka wholeheartedly pledge to appoint @ramanayaker to the parliament in the first instance of an occurrence of a vacancy in the national list. pic.twitter.com/xz68cEidAp",
        "Ramanayake was serving a four-year rigorous imprisonment sentence over charges of contempt court when President Wickremesinghe, after lobbying from politicians, actors, and others, granted him a pardon on the condition that he would not make any remarks that will be deemed to be in contempt of the courts.",
        "Sri Lanka president signs conditional pardon for ex MP Ranjan Ramanayake",
        "Ramanayake has yet to comment on whether he is interested in getting back into parliament as an SJB MP.",
        "Two former SJB MPs \u2014 Harin Fernando and Manusha Nanayakkara \u2013 who pushed for the actor-turned politician\u2019s pardon crossed over to to the government and have been alluding to more SJB parliamentarians joining the government or Wickremesinhe\u2019s United National Party (UNP) to help the president steer the country through economic reforms.",
        "Sri Lanka is in the midst of its worst economic crisis since Independence, and Wickremesinghe has been calling for the formation of an all-party government since he was appointed President. (Colombo/Aug26/2022)"
      ],
